  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How much do partners make over a lifetime?",
  "response": "The lifetime earnings of partners, particularly in professional services firms like law firms, accounting firms, and consulting firms, can vary widely depending on factors like the industry, location, the size and prestige of the firm, individual performance, and economic conditions. However, here are some general observations:\n\n1. **Law Firm Partners**: \n   - At large, prestigious law firms in major cities, equity partners can earn anywhere from several hundred thousand to several million dollars per year. Over a multi-decade career, this could tally into tens of millions of dollars. Non-equity partners typically earn less than equity partners.\n   \n2. **Accounting Firm Partners**: \n   - Partners at Big Four accounting firms (Deloitte, PwC, EY, KPMG) may earn from $300,000 to $1 million or more annually, depending on their role, location, and seniority. Smaller firms might offer lower ranges. Over a career, this could also reach into the millions.\n   \n3. **Consulting Firm Partners**: \n   - Partners at top-tier management consulting firms like McKinsey & Company, Boston Consulting Group, or Bain & Company might earn from $500,000 to several million dollars annually. Like law and accounting, lifetime earnings can easily be in the tens of millions depending on tenure and success.\n\n4. **Variables**:\n   - **Geography**: Regions with higher costs of living and more business activity typically offer higher compensation.\n   - **Firm Size and Prestige**: Bigger, more prestigious firms tend to offer higher compensation.\n   - **Equity vs. Non-Equity Status**: Equity partners generally have higher earning potential due to profit-sharing.\n   - **Performance and Tenure**: Long-term, successful partners who bring in significant business can see substantial earnings increases.\n\n5. **Wealth Accumulation**:\n   - Besides salary, partners at many firms receive significant bonuses, profit-sharing, and other incentives. They might also have opportunities for wealth accumulation through investments facilitated by their high income.\n\nIn summary, while it's challenging to pinpoint an exact lifetime earnings figure for partners due to the variability across industries and individual circumstances, partners at successful firms can accumulate considerable wealth over their careers.",
